1
00:02:39,280 --> 00:02:40,920
{\an8}This is the information Dad kept.

2
00:02:51,840 --> 00:02:53,600
{\an8}<i>The Blazing Tiger gang in Japan,</i>

3
00:02:54,200 --> 00:02:57,000
{\an8}they oppose Fire Phoenix.
They killed our people.

4
00:04:09,360 --> 00:04:10,680
I shot Rin myself.

5
00:04:12,560 --> 00:04:16,480
I told you I wouldn't let Fire Phoenix go,
but you saved Rin and returned her to 3C.

6
00:04:18,160 --> 00:04:19,480
Rin is with Fire Phoenix.

7
00:04:20,839 --> 00:04:23,200
She was ordered to protect Naruban,

8
00:04:23,280 --> 00:04:25,080
and Punlop commanded her to do everything.

9
00:04:25,160 --> 00:04:26,880
Exactly. That's his nature!

10
00:04:28,880 --> 00:04:32,280
He makes everyone a victim,
then tramples his way to the top.

11
00:04:32,360 --> 00:04:34,280
He abandons his subordinates,

12
00:04:34,360 --> 00:04:37,360
destroys everything
to avoid getting caught,

13
00:04:37,440 --> 00:04:40,360
and rises to power with protection.

14
00:04:40,440 --> 00:04:42,440
He's untouchable.

15
00:04:44,800 --> 00:04:45,760
Taiga.

16
00:04:45,840 --> 00:04:47,720
If this keeps up,

17
00:04:47,800 --> 00:04:49,880
one day Rin will die because of him.

18
00:04:50,760 --> 00:04:52,360
He kills anyone who's no longer useful.

19
00:04:56,880 --> 00:04:58,360
But if you care about Rin…

20
00:05:06,120 --> 00:05:08,240
turn the enemy into our side.

21
00:05:27,400 --> 00:05:29,120
We'll take revenge, unmask them…

22
00:05:30,760 --> 00:05:32,840
destroy Fire Phoenix by any means.

23
00:05:36,840 --> 00:05:38,200
But I'm asking you, Khanin.

24
00:05:39,960 --> 00:05:41,360
Don't hurt Rin.

25
00:05:43,760 --> 00:05:44,720
Alright.

26
00:05:46,040 --> 00:05:47,720
I won't touch Rin.

27
00:05:48,400 --> 00:05:50,560
From now on, her life is yours.

28
00:06:09,840 --> 00:06:10,880
Hey.

29
00:06:13,560 --> 00:06:16,200
How's the wound? Want to see a doctor?

30
00:06:17,200 --> 00:06:18,720
I went to the clinic nearby.

31
00:06:20,920 --> 00:06:24,160
Mr. Taiga has disappeared,
hasn't come to 3C Corp. at all.

32
00:06:27,840 --> 00:06:29,240
Did he do anything to you?

33
00:06:30,120 --> 00:06:31,760
I don't mean anything bad.

34
00:06:31,840 --> 00:06:33,480
I just mean,

35
00:06:33,560 --> 00:06:36,040
did Mr. Taiga help you

36
00:06:36,120 --> 00:06:38,400
and ask anything?

37
00:06:38,480 --> 00:06:41,680
Or did you two argue?
Why did he suddenly disappear?

38
00:06:43,760 --> 00:06:45,000
Nothing happened.

39
00:06:45,080 --> 00:06:46,200
Okay.

40
00:06:48,080 --> 00:06:51,000
Oh, I'll tell you first. On weekends,

41
00:06:51,080 --> 00:06:52,600
I'll be doing live sales.

42
00:06:52,680 --> 00:06:56,480
Right now at 3C Corp.,
I'm just gathering info.

43
00:06:57,160 --> 00:06:58,520
Info?

44
00:06:58,600 --> 00:06:59,600
What info?

45
00:06:59,680 --> 00:07:02,400
Everything about 3C Corp.

46
00:07:03,480 --> 00:07:04,600
But Techut said

47
00:07:04,680 --> 00:07:07,120
I'd work in my specialty field.

48
00:07:07,200 --> 00:07:09,600
Next week, I'll probably move
to a new department.

49
00:07:10,800 --> 00:07:14,360
He's rushing to set up this department
and managing everything himself.

50
00:07:16,680 --> 00:07:17,720
Be careful.

51
00:07:18,840 --> 00:07:20,480
I can handle myself.

52
00:07:23,360 --> 00:07:25,000
You stay safe too.

53
00:07:46,280 --> 00:07:47,520
I was worried about you.

54
00:07:48,360 --> 00:07:49,600
Where have you been?

55
00:07:53,560 --> 00:07:55,960
I was hurt, but I've recovered.

56
00:07:57,200 --> 00:07:58,360
What about you, Uncle?

57
00:08:00,680 --> 00:08:02,000
I can handle myself,

58
00:08:02,520 --> 00:08:03,560
you know that.

59
00:08:13,680 --> 00:08:15,280
My dad's hard drive.

60
00:08:18,840 --> 00:08:20,480
FIRE PHOENIX CASES

61
00:08:22,840 --> 00:08:26,080
FIRE PHOENIX CASES 2

62
00:08:29,120 --> 00:08:30,360
Rin.

63
00:08:31,920 --> 00:08:33,720
Did you dare lie to me?

64
00:08:39,120 --> 00:08:40,720
I lost it when we split up.

65
00:08:43,000 --> 00:08:45,480
I went over every inch,
but couldn't find it.

66
00:08:57,360 --> 00:08:58,960
I'm going to kill Taiga.

67
00:09:03,360 --> 00:09:04,600
Are you sure, Rin?

68
00:09:06,960 --> 00:09:09,480
I'll kill Taiga with my own hands.

69
00:09:11,200 --> 00:09:12,640
Do you trust me, Uncle?

70
00:09:20,640 --> 00:09:21,640
Fine.

71
00:09:22,800 --> 00:09:24,560
Taiga's life is yours.

72
00:09:27,320 --> 00:09:28,480
Kill him.

73
00:09:29,240 --> 00:09:30,920
Then return to protect Mr. Naruban,

74
00:09:31,680 --> 00:09:34,520
so he can work
for the future of everyone in the world.

75
00:10:34,080 --> 00:10:35,680
Sorry for coming into this room.

76
00:10:38,640 --> 00:10:40,240
You can come here anytime.

77
00:10:43,760 --> 00:10:44,920
Is your wound still hurting?

78
00:10:47,040 --> 00:10:48,040
It doesn't hurt anymore.

79
00:10:59,840 --> 00:11:01,280
Take care of yourself.

80
00:11:23,960 --> 00:11:25,560
<i>Fingerprint accepted.</i>

81
00:11:49,600 --> 00:11:50,600
What's this?

82
00:11:51,400 --> 00:11:53,560
Work here. No need to contact anyone.

83
00:11:53,640 --> 00:11:55,360
Do your own job,

84
00:11:55,440 --> 00:11:58,360
get paid, spend, relax.

85
00:12:08,120 --> 00:12:09,960
Here. Change into the uniform too.

86
00:12:14,200 --> 00:12:15,200
Okay.

87
00:12:28,440 --> 00:12:30,600
Dad has a new project,

88
00:12:31,320 --> 00:12:33,200
called 3C We Share.

89
00:12:33,280 --> 00:12:36,080
It provides clothes
for underprivileged kids

90
00:12:36,160 --> 00:12:39,960
and make outfits for bedridden patients
in nursing homes,

91
00:12:40,040 --> 00:12:42,640
all requested through the Hi app.

92
00:12:44,400 --> 00:12:47,080
So you want me to design the outfits?

93
00:12:48,960 --> 00:12:49,800
Yes.

94
00:12:50,560 --> 00:12:52,880
But you don't have to use the Kenji brand.

95
00:12:53,680 --> 00:12:56,600
It can be a collaboration
between 3C Corp. and you.

96
00:12:57,120 --> 00:12:57,960
How about that?

97
00:12:58,040 --> 00:12:59,280
Sounds good.

98
00:13:00,160 --> 00:13:02,520
I'd like to give back to society too.

99
00:13:03,120 --> 00:13:04,000
Deal.

100
00:13:18,120 --> 00:13:19,000
Come in.

101
00:13:23,440 --> 00:13:25,400
Is there something you need me to do?

102
00:13:28,800 --> 00:13:30,360
At that desk,

103
00:13:31,000 --> 00:13:33,000
take notes on the chemists' reports

104
00:13:33,080 --> 00:13:35,000
and summarize them for me.

105
00:13:35,600 --> 00:13:36,520
Okay.

106
00:13:37,160 --> 00:13:39,920
But if you're lazy, bored,
or tired of hard work

107
00:13:40,960 --> 00:13:42,080
and want an easier task…

108
00:13:46,320 --> 00:13:47,960
just call me.

109
00:13:48,960 --> 00:13:50,200
Okay.

110
00:13:50,280 --> 00:13:52,120
Thank you. I'll remember that.

111
00:13:53,600 --> 00:13:55,440
I'll start working now.

112
00:13:55,520 --> 00:13:56,760
Yeah.

113
00:14:10,840 --> 00:14:14,040
I pumped the coin and made enough profit
to hire five more top chemists.

114
00:14:15,600 --> 00:14:17,360
How much longer for the experiments?

115
00:14:18,000 --> 00:14:19,520
Depends on how much we invest.

116
00:14:23,360 --> 00:14:24,600
How many more millions?

117
00:14:26,080 --> 00:14:27,160
No need, Dad.

118
00:14:28,360 --> 00:14:32,680
I told you, the profits from our coins
are enough to invest plenty more.

119
00:14:34,800 --> 00:14:38,120
The part your sister's overseeing
is doing well.

120
00:14:38,920 --> 00:14:41,640
The news is even attracting
more investors.

121
00:14:43,000 --> 00:14:46,480
If you want to dominate the world,
just wait a bit.

122
00:14:47,040 --> 00:14:49,520
I'll give you more than that small app.

123
00:14:50,360 --> 00:14:53,360
I'll put the whole world in your hands.

124
00:15:08,760 --> 00:15:10,080
Alright.

125
00:15:10,160 --> 00:15:11,840
Thanks. See you tomorrow.

126
00:15:55,080 --> 00:15:56,560
Hello.

127
00:15:59,240 --> 00:16:01,800
Oh, I just got home.

128
00:16:02,800 --> 00:16:05,000
The report, right?

129
00:16:05,080 --> 00:16:07,240
I'll send it right away.

130
00:16:07,320 --> 00:16:09,240
I'm about to go into my room.

131
00:16:09,840 --> 00:16:12,200
I'll send it as soon as I get to my room.

132
00:16:13,000 --> 00:16:16,240
Not too long. Just a sec, please.

133
00:16:17,080 --> 00:16:18,280
Sure, of course.

134
00:16:20,160 --> 00:16:21,840
Got it.

135
00:16:22,520 --> 00:16:24,800
Okay, sure.

136
00:16:40,840 --> 00:16:43,280
Techut definitely has people watching me.

137
00:16:43,920 --> 00:16:47,640
Honestly, I have no idea what he's testing
under the building.

138
00:16:50,280 --> 00:16:51,960
If we could just get one sample.

139
00:16:54,320 --> 00:16:56,680
That's nearly impossible, Rin.

140
00:16:57,760 --> 00:17:02,320
Everyone who goes there gets checked,
both coming in and going out.

141
00:17:02,400 --> 00:17:04,280
They'd strip-search anyone if they could.

142
00:17:07,440 --> 00:17:10,520
I'll act compliant and make sure

143
00:17:10,599 --> 00:17:11,880
I don't raise suspicion.

144
00:17:12,680 --> 00:17:15,920
If I get the chance,
I'll get it out for you.

145
00:17:36,720 --> 00:17:39,960
Drive me. I'm going
to have lunch with Mr. Eric.

146
00:17:40,600 --> 00:17:41,600
Yes, sir.

147
00:17:52,920 --> 00:17:54,120
Interesting.

148
00:17:54,880 --> 00:17:57,440
It's a good project. Start it right away.

149
00:17:57,960 --> 00:17:59,520
Thank you, Dad.

150
00:18:01,520 --> 00:18:04,880
You've helped 3C Corp. in many ways.

151
00:18:06,240 --> 00:18:07,680
Do you like Thailand?

152
00:18:08,600 --> 00:18:10,320
Do you want to stay here permanently?

153
00:18:10,400 --> 00:18:11,920
Not yet, sir.

154
00:18:13,120 --> 00:18:15,680
Once I finish work here,
I'll go back home.

155
00:18:18,640 --> 00:18:21,280
Don't you ever think
of making Thailand your home?

156
00:18:22,920 --> 00:18:24,160
For me, a home

157
00:18:25,120 --> 00:18:27,600
isn't just land or buildings.

158
00:18:28,800 --> 00:18:31,440
A home means the people
you live your life with.

159
00:18:35,760 --> 00:18:40,040
I hope you find your warm home here
in Thailand soon.

160
00:19:12,800 --> 00:19:14,720
I'll go to the bathroom.

161
00:19:15,360 --> 00:19:16,400
Let's go.

162
00:19:26,640 --> 00:19:27,840
I'll go to the bathroom.

163
00:19:36,640 --> 00:19:40,240
Where are they going?
I've seen them leave many times already.

164
00:19:40,320 --> 00:19:43,080
Bathroom. Food poisoning
started yesterday.

165
00:19:44,080 --> 00:19:46,920
I see.

166
00:19:50,920 --> 00:19:52,800
You're working so hard!

167
00:19:52,880 --> 00:19:54,960
So tough, not stopping at all.

168
00:19:55,040 --> 00:19:56,560
It's a rush job.

169
00:20:00,000 --> 00:20:02,560
Carry on then. I won't bother you.

170
00:20:07,240 --> 00:20:09,400
How are you? Tired?

171
00:20:12,080 --> 00:20:13,400
I'm okay.

172
00:20:14,240 --> 00:20:16,960
There's a lot of paperwork.
I'll summarize it quickly.

173
00:20:19,680 --> 00:20:20,640
Ow!

174
00:20:21,360 --> 00:20:22,640
My stomach.

175
00:20:22,720 --> 00:20:25,200
Nature calls. Excuse me.

176
00:20:36,160 --> 00:20:37,880
Mr. Te.

177
00:20:38,880 --> 00:20:41,280
I'll be right back from the bathroom,

178
00:20:41,360 --> 00:20:42,560
then we can talk.

179
00:21:18,440 --> 00:21:19,760
Ow!

180
00:21:19,840 --> 00:21:20,960
Mr. Techut!

181
00:21:21,040 --> 00:21:22,640
- Get up, quickly!
- No, don't!

182
00:21:26,680 --> 00:21:27,560
What's wrong?

183
00:21:28,960 --> 00:21:30,800
My stomach hurts a little.

184
00:21:32,640 --> 00:21:33,520
Still?

185
00:21:36,280 --> 00:21:37,400
Want to see a doctor?

186
00:21:38,000 --> 00:21:39,120
Ow!

187
00:21:41,000 --> 00:21:43,000
Ow!

188
00:21:46,280 --> 00:21:47,400
Are you okay?

189
00:21:48,880 --> 00:21:50,360
I'm fine.

190
00:21:50,440 --> 00:21:52,200
Just need a short break.

191
00:21:52,280 --> 00:21:53,640
I'll get back to work soon.

192
00:21:56,280 --> 00:21:57,480
Then,

193
00:21:58,880 --> 00:22:00,040
let's go have some coffee.

194
00:22:02,920 --> 00:22:03,800
Okay.

195
00:22:08,840 --> 00:22:10,280
Thank you.

196
00:22:23,120 --> 00:22:24,200
Thank you.

197
00:22:24,280 --> 00:22:27,840
Getting out here and smelling the coffee
already makes me feel better.

198
00:22:27,920 --> 00:22:29,360
Gives me energy to work.

199
00:22:31,160 --> 00:22:32,640
If you ever get bored with work,

200
00:22:33,240 --> 00:22:34,520
just call me.

201
00:22:36,240 --> 00:22:38,960
Well, with a boss this kind,

202
00:22:39,040 --> 00:22:40,480
who'd dare get bored?

203
00:22:41,240 --> 00:22:44,200
I'll work my hardest for 3C Corp.

204
00:22:51,040 --> 00:22:54,160
Oh, break time's over. I have to go.

205
00:22:55,280 --> 00:22:56,360
Alright.

206
00:23:24,240 --> 00:23:25,680
Hello, Miss Ratee.

207
00:23:26,200 --> 00:23:27,600
Hello, Mr. Techut.

208
00:23:28,240 --> 00:23:29,240
After you.

209
00:23:37,600 --> 00:23:39,440
I'll take care of this one.

210
00:23:42,560 --> 00:23:43,640
Sure.

211
00:24:16,160 --> 00:24:17,960
Back to her room as usual, sir.

212
00:24:18,560 --> 00:24:20,080
Did any men come by?

213
00:24:20,160 --> 00:24:21,280
No, sir.

214
00:24:49,360 --> 00:24:50,560
Isn't your dad really rich?

215
00:24:51,880 --> 00:24:54,080
Yes, and?

216
00:24:54,680 --> 00:24:55,920
Send it to an overseas lab for testing.

217
00:24:57,680 --> 00:24:59,680
I know a bit about it myself.

218
00:25:03,960 --> 00:25:05,440
Better let a professional handle it.

219
00:25:05,520 --> 00:25:09,320
Wow, you can count on her.

220
00:25:10,840 --> 00:25:12,200
How long until we get the results?

221
00:25:14,400 --> 00:25:16,880
<i>I don't want you getting involved</i>
<i>with 3C Corp. like this, Ratee.</i>

222
00:25:22,000 --> 00:25:24,240
I'll do anything to help you.

223
00:25:24,320 --> 00:25:26,200
Just you.

224
00:25:26,280 --> 00:25:28,200
Nothing to do with Rin and the others.

225
00:25:32,280 --> 00:25:33,560
Okay.

226
00:25:33,640 --> 00:25:34,920
They can be a be involved a bit.

227
00:25:36,040 --> 00:25:40,360
Rin probably wants to know
what they're doing in 3C Corp.'s lab.

228
00:25:42,320 --> 00:25:43,920
3C Corp. has a lab?

229
00:25:46,480 --> 00:25:48,120
Why has Ms. Nun never mentioned this?

230
00:25:48,200 --> 00:25:51,720
This is the work of Naruban's eldest son,
whom he's backing.

231
00:25:53,080 --> 00:25:55,120
It has to be connected to Fire Phoenix.

232
00:26:17,920 --> 00:26:18,960
Sun.

233
00:26:19,800 --> 00:26:21,360
I'm begging you.

234
00:26:22,000 --> 00:26:26,000
Please leave some space
for the good memories between us.

235
00:26:26,840 --> 00:26:29,320
Don't push so hard
that I have to push you away.

236
00:26:30,040 --> 00:26:32,200
All this effort,

237
00:26:33,280 --> 00:26:35,200
it doesn't make me feel good at all.

238
00:26:35,960 --> 00:26:38,880
Calm down, Aru. Listen to me.

239
00:26:39,640 --> 00:26:41,920
I'm trading
this company's coins right now.

240
00:26:45,520 --> 00:26:47,160
It's 3C-Coin.

241
00:26:47,240 --> 00:26:50,720
At first, I invested tens of thousands
and made hundreds of thousands in profit.

242
00:26:50,800 --> 00:26:53,600
Then I invested hundreds of thousands
and got millions back.

243
00:26:53,680 --> 00:26:57,120
But I'm not using the money
to make up for mistakes.

244
00:26:57,720 --> 00:26:59,680
I just want you to know

245
00:26:59,760 --> 00:27:02,080
I can take care of my family now.

246
00:27:02,160 --> 00:27:05,800
And from now on,
if you want my help with anything,

247
00:27:06,680 --> 00:27:10,640
think of me. I'll always help.

248
00:27:12,880 --> 00:27:15,360
I won't bother you anymore.
I'm leaving now.

249
00:27:16,920 --> 00:27:17,960
Wait, Sun.

250
00:27:20,600 --> 00:27:23,000
What can 3C-Coin actually do?

251
00:27:23,080 --> 00:27:24,280
Tell me.

252
00:27:25,440 --> 00:27:28,160
3C Corp. uses its own coin

253
00:27:28,240 --> 00:27:30,480
for everything inside the Hi app.

254
00:27:30,560 --> 00:27:33,360
Soon, 3C-Coin will also be used for loans

255
00:27:33,440 --> 00:27:35,280
and safe investments,

256
00:27:35,360 --> 00:27:36,520
all secured with digital encryption.

257
00:27:37,440 --> 00:27:41,040
Everything's done through a computer
that never lies.

258
00:27:41,800 --> 00:27:44,160
Anyone can do it themselves.

259
00:27:44,680 --> 00:27:46,720
You mean Fire Phoenix

260
00:27:46,800 --> 00:27:49,080
would use 3C-Coin
to launder money illegally?

261
00:27:50,800 --> 00:27:51,800
Yes.

262
00:27:52,720 --> 00:27:54,720
They run it like a pyramid scheme.

263
00:27:54,800 --> 00:27:58,000
Start by recruiting people
to invest in the coin,

264
00:27:58,080 --> 00:27:59,760
find a credible frontman,

265
00:27:59,840 --> 00:28:03,960
someone famous,
with social influence, a stock expert,

266
00:28:04,680 --> 00:28:06,640
to attract investors,

267
00:28:07,400 --> 00:28:10,000
and have solid backing,

268
00:28:10,080 --> 00:28:11,680
like some powerful officials.

269
00:28:11,760 --> 00:28:14,280
They offer insane returns,

270
00:28:14,360 --> 00:28:16,120
so people stop thinking rationally,

271
00:28:16,200 --> 00:28:17,720
and don't consider the consequences.

272
00:28:17,800 --> 00:28:19,200
They use people's greed

273
00:28:19,920 --> 00:28:21,360
to destroy their own lives.

274
00:28:28,560 --> 00:28:31,800
Sun explained 3C-Coin to me.

275
00:28:32,400 --> 00:28:36,000
I'm still a bit confused,
but here's what I got.

276
00:28:36,080 --> 00:28:40,280
The coin makes Mr. Naruban huge profits.

277
00:28:40,360 --> 00:28:41,920
But on the other hand,

278
00:28:42,000 --> 00:28:45,360
it can also be used
as a channel for illegal activities,

279
00:28:45,440 --> 00:28:47,360
since no one can track it yet.

280
00:28:47,440 --> 00:28:50,080
Like the money used for the lab?

281
00:28:51,200 --> 00:28:52,320
Exactly.

282
00:28:57,640 --> 00:29:00,560
Aru, I'll ask you straight.

283
00:29:00,640 --> 00:29:01,840
Yeah.

284
00:29:03,600 --> 00:29:05,240
If Sun helps us…

285
00:29:06,800 --> 00:29:07,960
Rin.

286
00:29:08,520 --> 00:29:11,960
Are you asking to get Sun to help us too?

287
00:29:46,120 --> 00:29:48,520
Rin. This is Rin.

288
00:29:51,400 --> 00:29:55,680
Well, what do you need me
to help with? Just tell me.

289
00:29:55,760 --> 00:29:57,680
We want to know about 3C-Coin.

290
00:29:58,920 --> 00:30:01,440
In-depth, not just trading stuff.

291
00:30:01,520 --> 00:30:03,880
Why do you want to know?

292
00:30:05,240 --> 00:30:06,920
It's not illegal, right?

293
00:30:08,400 --> 00:30:12,680
No. We're trying
to prevent illegal activities.

294
00:30:15,800 --> 00:30:17,840
We want you to work for Techut.

295
00:30:32,440 --> 00:30:33,880
Find the hard drive.

296
00:30:34,480 --> 00:30:35,720
Anyone in the way,

297
00:30:36,360 --> 00:30:37,720
kill them all.

298
00:30:55,440 --> 00:30:58,760
I've got the file.
Where do you want me to deliver it?

299
00:31:00,320 --> 00:31:01,280
Got it.

300
00:31:32,880 --> 00:31:34,360
Hey!

301
00:31:36,840 --> 00:31:38,240
Ugh!

302
00:32:41,320 --> 00:32:43,000
Are you okay? Let's go.

303
00:32:47,320 --> 00:32:48,360
Come here.

304
00:34:19,880 --> 00:34:21,159
Hey, wait!

305
00:34:21,239 --> 00:34:22,320
It's me.

306
00:34:25,199 --> 00:34:28,639
Don't stay here. You'll die if you do.
Let's go.

307
00:34:28,719 --> 00:34:29,960
What do they want?

308
00:34:30,480 --> 00:34:32,280
Or are they after Rin?

309
00:34:32,360 --> 00:34:33,719
Don't worry about anyone else. Go.

310
00:34:33,800 --> 00:34:36,280
- Rin isn't anyone else! She's my friend.
- Go, Aru!

311
00:34:36,360 --> 00:34:39,120
- Let me call Rin first!
- We'll deal with that later.

312
00:34:42,639 --> 00:34:43,840
Whose house is this?

313
00:34:45,560 --> 00:34:46,800
My house.

314
00:34:51,120 --> 00:34:53,280
You said you didn't have a home.

315
00:34:56,159 --> 00:34:59,320
Someone like Dhammatat
can only afford a doghouse.

316
00:35:01,840 --> 00:35:03,200
Madam!

317
00:35:03,280 --> 00:35:04,520
If you didn't bark for once,

318
00:35:04,600 --> 00:35:06,120
you won't enjoy your meal?

319
00:35:06,720 --> 00:35:07,720
Wait.

320
00:35:07,800 --> 00:35:09,120
Before you two start fighting,

321
00:35:09,200 --> 00:35:10,720
clarify this first.

322
00:35:10,800 --> 00:35:12,400
Why am I here?

323
00:35:13,360 --> 00:35:14,680
To survive.

324
00:35:14,760 --> 00:35:17,600
Going to wait there
and get killed in your little hole?

325
00:35:19,400 --> 00:35:22,400
Any leftover bones?
Bring them so he can gnaw a bit.

326
00:35:24,680 --> 00:35:26,160
Some people just don't appreciate help.

327
00:35:29,360 --> 00:35:33,200
You can stay here. This is my place.
I bought it ages ago.

328
00:35:33,280 --> 00:35:35,480
No one will ever find you.

329
00:35:36,560 --> 00:35:39,120
But I still have work at 3C Corp.

330
00:35:40,480 --> 00:35:42,720
I'll hire a driver to shuttle you.

331
00:35:42,800 --> 00:35:44,400
Get off the car
a bit away from the building,

332
00:35:44,480 --> 00:35:47,400
act like you're coming
from the skytrain, then walk in.

333
00:35:48,800 --> 00:35:51,040
Is it really that dangerous?

334
00:35:54,360 --> 00:35:55,760
What about Rin?

335
00:35:58,200 --> 00:35:59,640
Someone already helped her.

336
00:36:08,680 --> 00:36:09,920
Mr. Taiga?

337
00:36:12,120 --> 00:36:13,640
Yes.

338
00:36:18,160 --> 00:36:19,360
- Come here.
- What?

339
00:36:21,040 --> 00:36:22,320
I'm not a dog, you know.

340
00:36:24,760 --> 00:36:25,800
So…

341
00:36:27,480 --> 00:36:28,880
She loves Mr. Taiga?

342
00:36:32,000 --> 00:36:33,360
- Yeah.
- So,

343
00:36:34,440 --> 00:36:36,320
where did Mr. Taiga take Rin?

344
00:36:54,920 --> 00:36:56,080
Be careful.

345
00:37:22,960 --> 00:37:24,080
Thank you.

346
00:38:17,840 --> 00:38:19,000
I helped you…

347
00:38:25,040 --> 00:38:26,600
because you're still useful to me.

348
00:39:06,360 --> 00:39:08,080
Make yourself comfortable.

349
00:39:08,640 --> 00:39:10,600
Inseethong Farm welcomes you.

350
00:39:11,360 --> 00:39:12,480
Thank you.

351
00:39:13,480 --> 00:39:15,760
How's your father doing?

352
00:39:18,200 --> 00:39:19,400
Same as usual.

353
00:39:20,320 --> 00:39:22,640
He's been doing physical therapy
a lot lately,

354
00:39:22,720 --> 00:39:24,400
so he can walk a few steps now.

355
00:44:30,000 --> 00:44:31,680
{\an8}Do you want to tell me anything?

356
00:44:33,560 --> 00:44:35,160
{\an8}<i>Your person took mine.</i>

357
00:44:35,240 --> 00:44:37,080
{\an8}<i>Tell Taiga not to mess with Rin.</i>

358
00:44:37,160 --> 00:44:39,320
{\an8}What if they both want to be together?

359
00:44:39,400 --> 00:44:41,560
{\an8}Uncle! Hey, Uncle!

360
00:44:41,640 --> 00:44:45,760
{\an8}Indhorn, guess I'll have
to pay you a visit, cousin.

361
00:44:45,840 --> 00:44:47,040
{\an8}Rin!

362
00:45:23,000 --> 00:45:25,520
Subtitle translation by:
Chomchanach Yanaharn

